    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-12-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-12-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="645"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d645">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Choate</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-12-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 21, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 262.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose for your information copy of
                        correspondence,<note n="1" xml:id="d645fn1">(Inclosures:) Messrs. Hopkins
                        &amp; Hopkins to Mr. Hay, December 12, 1899, and December 15, 1899, printed
                            <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>.</note> as indicated below, in regard to the
                    reported seizure by Her Majesty’s cruiser <hi rend="italic">Partridge</hi> of
                    the British steamers <hi rend="italic">Mashona</hi> and <hi rend="italic"
                        >Maria</hi> off the east coast of Africa, portions of the cargoes of which,
                    consisting of general merchandise, are the property of Messrs. Flint, Eddy &amp;
                    Co.</p>
                <p>You are instructed to bring the matter to the attention of the British
                    Government, and to inquire as to the circumstances and legality of the seizure.
                    If it was illegal, you will request prompt action and restitution in the
                    case.</p>
                <p>The United States consul at Lourenço Marquez will be instructed to use all proper
                    efforts to protect the rights of Messrs. Flint, Eddy &amp; Co.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
